      "morph": "[imp. & p. p. Polled (?); p. pr. & vb. n. Polling.]",
      "usage": [],
      "wordforms": [],
      "entry_synonyms": [],
      "entry_fields": [],
      "senses": [
        {
          "sn": "1.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "To remove the poll or head of; hence, to remove the top or end of; to clip; to lop; to shear; as, to poll the head; to poll a tree."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "When he [Absalom] pollled his head.",
            "His death did so grieve them that they polled themselves; they clipped off their horse and mule's hairs."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "2.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "To cut off; to remove by clipping, shearing, etc.; to mow or crop; -- sometimes with off; as, to poll the hair; to poll wool; to poll grass."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "Who, as he polled off his dart's head, so sure he had decreed That all the counsels of their war he would poll off like it."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "3.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "To extort from; to plunder; to strip."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "Which polls and pills the poor in piteous wise."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "4.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "To impose a tax upon."
          ],
          "quotes": [],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "5.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "To pay as one's personal tax."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "The man that polled but twelve pence for his head."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "6.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "To enter, as polls or persons, in a list or register; to enroll, esp. for purposes of taxation; to enumerate one by one."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "Polling the reformed churches whether they equalize in number those of his three kingdoms."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "7.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "To register or deposit, as a vote; to elicit or call forth, as votes or voters; as, he polled a hundred votes more than his opponent."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "And poll for points of faith his trusty vote."
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "8.",
          "fields": [
            "(Law)"
          ],
          "defs": [
            "To cut or shave smooth or even; to cut in a straight line without indentation; as, a polled deed. See Dee<?/ poll."
          ],
          "quotes": [],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        }
      ]
